<div id="review_2649298228" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2649298228" />
    <a title="Archan Ray" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/19113175-archan-ray"><img alt="Archan Ray" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1365161794p2/19113175.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2649298228?book_show_action=true">Aug 17, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Archan Ray" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Archan Ray" href="/user/show/19113175-archan-ray">Archan Ray</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780241284407" href="/book/show/31340713-and-quiet-flows-the-don">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2649298228" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11933260362222413726">I think there are 3 kinds of books: 1. ones you read and forget after sometime, 2. you read pondering the whole time about the implications the events have on its subjects. you remember these text, and are ready to swear by them, and 3. the ones which when you&apos;re reading your soul is shaken. the experiences of each characters become your experiences. I&apos;m glad to say I found this book to be of the third kind.</span>
  <span id="freeText11933260362222413726" style="display:none">I think there are 3 kinds of books: 1. ones you read and forget after sometime, 2. you read pondering the whole time about the implications the events have on its subjects. you remember these text, and are ready to swear by them, and 3. the ones which when you're reading your soul is shaken. the experiences of each characters become your experiences. I'm glad to say I found this book to be of the third kind.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11933260362222413726" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


